43 (b) Any parent or legal guardian of a child who is taken into temporary protective custody
44 pursuant to Code Section 15-11-131 shall have the right to obtain an independent medical
45 evaluation and a specialty consultation of such child at his or her own expense unless
46 prohibited by court order. Physicians and medical professionals, law enforcement officers,
47 and DFCS shall cooperate as may reasonably be necessary to facilitate any independent
48 medical evaluation or specialty consultation for such child.
49 (c) At any hearing concerning a child before the court in a dependency proceeding
50 pursuant to this article, the court shall consider the results from any independent medical
51 evaluation or specialty consultation of such child.
52 (d) No adjudication hearing scheduled in accordance with Part 8 of this article shall be
53 continued solely because the results from an independent medical evaluation or specialty
54 consultation of the child before the court are unavailable."
55 SECTION 3.
56 This Act shall become effective upon its approval by the Governor or upon its becoming law
57 without such approval and shall apply to any legal action filed on or after such effective date.
58 SECTION 4.
59 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
